.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH problem 1  "problem " 
.SH NAME
problem \- Manage problems (ITIL): root causes behind recurring incidents
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBproblem\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage problems (ITIL): root causes behind recurring incidents
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
problem\-open(1)
Open a new problem
.TP
problem\-list(1)
List problems, optionally filtered by status
.TP
problem\-show(1)
Show one problem by id
.TP
problem\-link(1)
Link an incident to a problem
.TP
problem\-known\-error(1)
Promote a problem to a known error with a root cause
.TP
problem\-hypothesis\-add(1)
Add a root\-cause hypothesis to a problem
.TP
problem\-hypothesis\-list(1)
List a problem\*(Aqs hypotheses
.TP
problem\-hypothesis\-status(1)
Set a hypothesis\*(Aqs status: created|validating|confirmed|rejected
.TP
problem\-escalate(1)
Escalate a problem to dvalin as a BUG/FEAT (structured bus message)
.TP
problem\-close(1)
Close a problem
.TP
problem\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
